title: Honoring Mary-Jane Dilberian upon the occasion of her designation as recipient of the 2011 Non-Judicial Court Employee Award by The Kings County Criminal Bar Association
fulltext:
LEGISLATIVE RESOLUTION honoring Mary-Jane Dilberian upon the occasion of
her  designation  as  recipient  of the 2011 Non-Judicial Court Employee
Award by The Kings County Criminal Bar Association

WHEREAS, Individuals who give of their time and energies and  serve  the
best interests of their communities are an asset beyond remuneration and
cannot be sufficiently extolled; and
  WHEREAS,  Mary-Jane Dilberian has given not only of her time and ener-
gies but also of her competence, intelligence and leadership and  conse-
quently has been designated for special honor; and
  WHEREAS,  This  Legislative  Body  is  justly proud to honor Mary-Jane
Dilberian upon the occasion of her designation as recipient of the  2011
Non-Judicial Court Employee Award by The Kings County Criminal Bar Asso-
ciation,  to  be celebrated at its 2011 Annual Dinner Dance on Saturday,
February 5, 2011, at Russo's On The Bay in Howard Beach, New York; and
  WHEREAS, Mary-Jane Dilberian is receiving  this  auspicious  award  in
recognition of her many years of superb service in the court system; and
  WHEREAS,  A  lifelong  resident  of  Kings County, New York, Mary-Jane
Dilberian is a graduate of Edward R. Murrow High School and Kingsborough
Community College; and
  WHEREAS, In 1999, Mary-Jane Dilberian entered the court  system  as  a
Court Assistant in Richmond County Criminal Court; and
  WHEREAS,  Eight years later, in 2007, Mary-Jane Dilberian was promoted
to Senior Court Clerk and was assigned to Kings  County  Supreme  Court;
and
  WHEREAS,  Mary-Jane  Dilberian was assigned to work with Judge Michael
Brennan in January of 2008; due largely to her hard work and dedication,
today she makes his courtroom run efficiently and effectively; and
  WHEREAS, Mary-Jane Dilberian is the loving and proud mother of her two
children, Samantha Marie and Private Bryan Dilberian, both of whom  feel
privileged to be a part of her life and rejoice in her achievements; and
  WHEREAS,  Throughout  her  career, Mary-Jane Dilberian has shown dedi-
cation and commitment, fulfilling her job duties in the highest  profes-
sional manner and with the most scrupulous effort; and
  WHEREAS,  It  is the sense of this Legislative Body that when individ-
uals of such noble aims and accomplishments are brought  to  our  atten-
tion,  they  should  be celebrated and recognized by all the citizens of
the great State of New York; now, therefore, be it
  RESOLVED, That this Legislative Body pause  in  its  deliberations  to
honor Mary-Jane DiIberian upon the occasion of her designation as recip-
ient  of  the 2011 Non-Judicial Court Employee Award by The Kings County
Criminal Bar Association; and be it further
  RESOLVED, That a copy of this Resolution, suitably engrossed, be tran-
smitted to Mary-Jane Dilberian.
